    <fr:title text="Taylor polynomial">Taylor polynomial</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
    <fr:source-path>/Users/longie/forest/trees/FA-0003.tree</fr:source-path>
    <fr:date>
      <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
      <fr:month>5</fr:month>
      <fr:day>26</fr:day>
    </fr:date>
    <fr:authors>
      <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
    </fr:authors>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>A Taylor polynomial of a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a polynomial that approximates the function around a specific point. For a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> that is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> times differentiable at a point <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex>, the Taylor polynomial of degree <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> is:</fr:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[P_n(x) = \sum _{k=0}^{n} \frac {f^{(k)}(a)}{k!}(x-a)^k]]></fr:tex>
  </fr:mainmatter>
